# Figma wireframe layout idea

Frame: Desktop 1440 × 3000
Grid: 12 columns, Margin 80, Gutter 20 (optional)

A) Header / Navbar (Height 72)
• Left: Logo
• Right: Home / About / Facts / Gallery
• Background: dark w/ slight blur (optional)

B) Hero (Height ~700)

Auto Layout: horizontal
• Left column (width ~520)
• H1 Planet name (big)
• Subtitle (1–2 lines)
• 2 buttons
• Right column (width ~620)
• Big rounded image card (planet)

C) About (Height ~650)

Two-column
• Left: Image (rounded)
• Right: Text block with:
• Heading
• Paragraph
• Bullet list

D) Facts (Height ~600)
• Title + short text
• Cards grid (6 cards)
• 3 cards per row
• Card style: subtle panel + border + radius 18

E) Gallery (Height ~650)
• Title + short text
• Image grid 3×2 (6 images)
• Each image: same height (220), radius 18

F) Footer (Height ~120)
• Left: “Created by…”
• Right: “Sources…”

Figma tip: Make components for:
• Button
• Fact card
• Gallery image tile

